what bhikkhunis can do to uplift the buddhist tradition ho center for buddhist studies at stanford skip to main content area home home about the center events people academics research resources partners related links search this site ho center for buddhist studies at stanford what bhikkhunis can do to uplift the buddhist tradition date thu may 21 2009 10 30am location hartley conference center mitchell building earth sciences program series program series buddhism in the modern world 2008 09 speaker s name affiliation ven dhammananda chatsumarn kabilsingh ph d associate professor thammasat university bangkok the ven dhammananda looks at the success of the bhikkhuni sangha order of nuns during the buddha's time in contrast to the bhikkhuni or bhiksuni sangha in taiwan as it exists today she provides a glimpse of four centers where bhiksunis play a prominent role these four centers comprise hua fan college fo guang shan tzu chi foundation and dharma drum mountain speaker's bio speaker s bio on february 28 2003 chatsumarn kabilsingh ordained bhikkhuni dhammananda became the first thai woman to receive full ordination as a theravadin nun she earned a ph d in buddhist studies from maghda university in india and has taught at maha chula sangha university and at thammasat university currently venerable bhikkhuni dhammananda is abbot of the only temple in thailand where there are fully ordained nuns stanford university international comparative & area studies department of religious studies ho center for buddhist studies at stanford stanford university all rights reserved stanford ca 94305 site development by wired moon
